## Agent Roles

### Architect Agent

**Purpose:** Design system structure and make architectural decisions

**Responsibilities:**
- Review PRDs and create technical designs
- Define module boundaries and interfaces
- Ensure patterns are consistent
- Approve significant structural changes

**Access:**
- Read: All files
- Write: docs/architecture/, ARCHITECTURE.md

**Invocation:**
```
@architect Review this PRD and propose a technical design.
```

---

### Developer Agent

**Purpose:** Implement features according to specifications

**Responsibilities:**
- Write code following existing patterns
- Create unit tests for new code
- Fix bugs and handle edge cases
- Refactor when directed

**Access:**
- Read: All files
- Write: src/, tests/

**Invocation:**
```
@developer Implement [feature] according to [PRD link].
```

---

### Reviewer Agent

**Purpose:** Check code quality and catch issues

**Responsibilities:**
- Review code changes for bugs
- Verify adherence to patterns
- Check security concerns
- Suggest improvements

**Access:**
- Read: All files
- Write: None (comments only)

**Invocation:**
```
@reviewer Review the changes in [files/PR].
```

---

### Tester Agent

**Purpose:** Create and maintain test coverage

**Responsibilities:**
- Write integration tests
- Create test fixtures and mocks
- Identify edge cases
- Verify acceptance criteria

**Access:**
- Read: All files
- Write: tests/, fixtures/

**Invocation:**
```
@tester Write tests for [feature] covering [scenarios].
```

